The paper focuses on solving Visual Question Answering (VQA) problems, which requires techniques from both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel Focused Dynamic Attention (FDA) model that employs off-the-shelf object detector to identify important regions and fuse the information from the regions and global features via an LSTM unit, which involves techniques from cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed model on a large-scale benchmark dataset, VQA, which involves techniques from cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
